# photocull (Photos) scan options — one option per line, '#' starts a comment.
#
# Copy this file to your working folder as `photos.args` and edit it. The app
# reads it on launch (the working folder is the one you pick, or $PHOTOCULL_HOME,
# or ~/.photocull).
#
# NOTE: comments must be on their OWN line; the launcher only strips whole-line
# comments, so a '#' after a value would be passed to the program by mistake.

# ---- Subset: what to scan (uncomment one or combine) ----
--smart-album recently-added
# --album "Iceland 2024"
# --since 2025-01-01
# --until 2025-12-31
# --limit 1000
# --include-favorites          # favourites are excluded by default

# ---- Detection signals: which kinds of photos to flag ----
# All eight possible signals are enabled below. To narrow detection, drop names
# from this list or add an --exclude-signals line.
#   blur      -> Blurry            dark      -> Too dark
#   contrast  -> Low contrast      noise     -> Noisy
#   exposure  -> Bad exposure      aesthetic -> Low aesthetic (Vision)
#   utility   -> Utility/screenshot (Vision)
#   face      -> Poor face capture  (Vision)
--signals blur,dark,contrast,noise,exposure,aesthetic,utility,face
# --exclude-signals aesthetic,utility

# ---- Signal thresholds (defaults shown; uncomment a line to override) ----
# --blur 100.0
# --blur-hard 35.0
# --dark 50.0
# --dark-hard 25.0
# --contrast 18.0
# --noise 7.0
# --aesthetic -0.10
# --face 0.30

# ---- Near-duplicates / bursts ----
--dedupe
# --dedupe-threshold 0.3         # lower = stricter / safer

# ---- Review albums ----
--albums-by signal               # one album per defect; use 'tier' for grouped albums
# --album-prefix photocull
# --replace-albums               # delete previous photocull albums first

# ---- iCloud ----
# --no-download                  # skip (don't download) iCloud-only originals
